<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading">Small-Scale Stirling Engines</h3>



<div style=3D"height:20px" aria-hidden=3D"true" class=3D"wp-block-spacer"><=
/div>



<ul class=3D"wp-block-list">
<li>Small nuclear power systems using Stirling technology could provide lon=
g-duration electric power for probes, landers, rovers, and communication re=
peaters on the Moon or Mars.</li>



<li>These systems would convert heat from the decay of radioisotope fuel in=
to usable electricity to support spacecraft mobility, science instruments, =
and communications.</li>



<li>Each system would use a single convertor and balancer assembly to conve=
rt heat from an isotope source and eliminate residual dynamic disturbance.<=
/li>



<li>Small Stirling RPS could achieve 15% to 25% conversion efficiency, prod=
ucing 20=E2=80=9350 watts of usable electrical power.</li>
</ul>


