<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading alignwide" id=3D"fsp">Fission Surface Power</=
h2>



<div style=3D"height:20px" aria-hidden=3D"true" class=3D"wp-block-spacer"><=
/div>



<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading">Power Conversion</h3>



<div style=3D"height:20px" aria-hidden=3D"true" class=3D"wp-block-spacer"><=
/div>



<p>The power conversion subsystem is a central component in systems that us=
e fission surface power (FSP) and nuclear electric propulsion (NEP), transf=
orming a reactor=E2=80=99s thermal energy into usable electrical power for =
surface operations or spacecraft propulsion. Efficient and reliable energy =
conversion is essential for enabling long-duration missions.</p>



<p>NASA Glenn is developing advanced high-efficiency power conversion techn=
ologies, such as free-piston Stirling and closed Brayton cycle convertors, =
to support these systems. Work focuses on improving thermal-to-electric con=
version efficiency, enhancing long-term reliability, and reducing mass to e=
nable sustainable missions to the Moon and Mars.</p>


