<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading">Radiation Effects</h3>



<div style=3D"height:20px" aria-hidden=3D"true" class=3D"wp-block-spacer"><=
/div>



<p>Radiation is ubiquitous in space. In addition to natural background radi=
ation, some NASA missions will induce harsh radiation. NASA is advancing te=
chnology for a nuclear reactor that would provide surface power for human s=
pace exploration. This reactor will irradiate electronics, sensors, structu=
ral materials, heat-rejection mechanisms, power conversion systems, and mos=
t other technologies flown on the mission.</p>



<p>The effects of radiation on the various systems associated with this the=
rmal energy source need to be understood to ensure a successful mission. To=
 investigate radiation effects, NASA has conducted irradiation experiments,=
 used radiation transport and neutron transmutation models, assessed potent=
ial testing facilities, and more. This work is conducted in close collabora=
tion with the U.S. Department of Energy.</p>


