<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading alignwide" id=3D"atm">Aircraft Thermal Manage=
ment</h2>



<div style=3D"height:20px" aria-hidden=3D"true" class=3D"wp-block-spacer"><=
/div>



<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading">Thermal Recovery Energy Efficient System (TR=
EES)</h3>



<div style=3D"height:20px" aria-hidden=3D"true" class=3D"wp-block-spacer"><=
/div>



<p>The Thermal Recovery Energy Efficient System (TREES), developed at NASA =
Glenn, demonstrates how thermoacoustic waves can be used to manage heat. Ai=
rcraft, spacecraft, and power systems often generate high-grade waste heat,=
 which can pose challenges for thermal control.</p>



<p>TREES harnesses this thermal energy and uses oscillating pressure waves =
to convert high-grade waste heat into low-grade waste heat. This process cr=
itically reduces the burden on heat rejection systems and improves overall =
energy efficiency.</p>


